NICOSIA , Cyprus -LRB- AP -RRB- Two people were killed and five were injured as Cyprus was jolted by its strongest earthquake in 42 years .
The tremors Thursday night were also felt across the Mediterranean in Lebanon and northern Israel .
On the island of Cyprus , 24 villages in the the Troodos mountain range were affected , the government said .
In one , Arodhes , a town of several hundred people , most of the homes collapsed .
Villagers fled into the streets and many spent the night in cars as up to 30 aftershocks joggled the ground and landslides covered mountain roads .
Charilaos Hadjigeorghiou , 73 , and his wife , Stella , 65 , were crushed to death in their bed when their home collapsed in the village of Miliou , 55 kilometers -LRB- 35 miles -RRB- west of the capital , Nicosia .
The quake struck at 11:02 p.m. -LRB- 2002 GMT -RRB- .
Government chief seismologist Kyriacos Solomis said it had a preliminary magnitude of 5.2 .
A quake of magnitude 5 can cause considerable damage .
A major quake in the same area of western Cyprus killed dozens in 1953 .
There were no immediate reports of injuries or damage in Lebanon or Israel .
